## Complete MCP C# SDK API Reference

Based on exploration of the **ModelContextProtocol 1.2.0**, **ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore 1.2.0**, and **ModelContextProtocol.Core 1.2.0** NuGet packages, here's the complete API for ASP.NET Core HTTP/SSE transport, tools, and resources:

---

### 1. **HTTP/SSE Transport Registration in ASP.NET Core**

#### Primary Registration Method:
```csharp
// In Program.cs or Startup.cs
var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Register the MCP Server with DI
builder.Services
    .AddMcpServer(configureOptions =>
    {
        // Configure McpServerOptions here
    })
    .WithHttpTransport(configureTransport =>
    {
        // Configure HttpServerTransportOptions
        configureTransport.ConfigureSessionOptions = async (context, options) =>
        {
            // Configure per-session McpServerOptions with access to HttpContext
        };

        configureTransport.RunSessionHandler = async (context, server, cancellationToken) =>
        {
            // Optional callback for running logic before/after session
        };

        // Optional: Enable legacy SSE support
        // configureTransport.EnableLegacySse = true;
    })
    .AddAuthorizationFilters();  // For ASP.NET Core [Authorize] support

var app = builder.Build();

// Map HTTP endpoints for MCP Streamable HTTP transport
app.MapMcp("/mcp");  // Route pattern prefix

app.Run();
```

#### Method Signatures:

**`AddMcpServer` (Main registration point)**
```csharp
// Namespace: Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection
IMcpServerBuilder AddMcpServer(
    this IServiceCollection services,
    Action<ModelContextProtocol.Server.McpServerOptions> configureOptions);
```

**`WithHttpTransport` (Enable HTTP/SSE transport)**
```csharp
// Namespace: Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection
IMcpServerBuilder WithHttpTransport(
    this IMcpServerBuilder builder,
    Action<ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore.HttpServerTransportOptions> configureOptions);
```

**`MapMcp` (Map HTTP endpoints)**
```csharp
// Namespace: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Builder
IEndpointConventionBuilder MapMcp(
    this IEndpointRouteBuilder endpoints,
    string pattern);
```

**`AddAuthorizationFilters` (Enable ASP.NET Core authorization)**
```csharp
// Namespace: Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection
IMcpServerBuilder AddAuthorizationFilters(
    this IMcpServerBuilder builder);
```

#### HttpServerTransportOptions Configuration:
- **`ConfigureSessionOptions`**: Async callback for per-session MCP configuration with `HttpContext` access
- **`RunSessionHandler`**: Async callback for session lifecycle hooks (runs before/after session)
- **`EnableLegacySse`**: Boolean to enable legacy SSE endpoints at `/sse` and `/message` (2024-11-05 spec)
- **`IdleTimeout`**: TimeSpan for idle session timeout
- **`TimeProvider`**: Custom time provider for testing

---

### 2. **MCP Tools**

#### Attribute Names & Namespaces:

```csharp
// Namespace: ModelContextProtocol.Server

// For class-level discovery
[McpServerToolType]
public class MyToolClass
{
    // Mark individual methods as tools
    [McpServerTool(Name = "my_tool", Description = "...")]
    public string MyTool(string param1, int param2)
    {
        return "result";
    }
}
```

#### Registration Methods:

```csharp
// Namespace: Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection

// Option 1: Register generic type (scans for [McpServerTool] attributes)
builder
    .WithTools<MyToolClass>(jsonSerializerOptions)
    .WithTools<MyToolClass>(instance, jsonSerializerOptions);

// Option 2: Register from assembly
builder.WithToolsFromAssembly(
    assembly: Assembly.GetExecutingAssembly(),
    serializerOptions: jsonSerializerOptions);

// Option 3: Register pre-built tool instances
builder.WithTools(new[] { tool1, tool2 });

// Option 4: Register tool types
builder.WithTools(new[] { typeof(MyToolClass) }, jsonSerializerOptions);
```

#### Method Signatures:

```csharp
// Generic registration
IMcpServerBuilder WithTools<TToolType>(
    this IMcpServerBuilder builder,
    JsonSerializerOptions? serializerOptions = null);

IMcpServerBuilder WithTools<TToolType>(
    this IMcpServerBuilder builder,
    TToolType target,
    JsonSerializerOptions? serializerOptions = null);

// Assembly-based discovery
IMcpServerBuilder WithToolsFromAssembly(
    this IMcpServerBuilder builder,
    Assembly? toolAssembly = null,
    JsonSerializerOptions? serializerOptions = null);

// Direct tool registration
IMcpServerBuilder WithTools(
    this IMcpServerBuilder builder,
    IEnumerable<ModelContextProtocol.Server.McpServerTool> tools);

IMcpServerBuilder WithTools(
    this IMcpServerBuilder builder,
    IEnumerable<Type> toolTypes,
    JsonSerializerOptions? serializerOptions = null);
```

#### Attribute Details:

**`[McpServerToolType]`** - Class-level attribute
```csharp
// Namespace: ModelContextProtocol.Server
[AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Class)]
public class McpServerToolTypeAttribute
```
- Marks a class for automatic tool discovery via `WithToolsFromAssembly`
- Required methods must have `[McpServerTool]` attribute

**`[McpServerTool]`** - Method-level attribute
```csharp
// Namespace: ModelContextProtocol.Server
[AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Method)]
public class McpServerToolAttribute
```
- Marks individual methods as MCP tools
- Parameters sourced from `CallToolRequestParams.Arguments` dictionary
- Automatically handles parameter marshaling and return value serialization

